Juveniles (
Fig. 1
): Background of midventral body silvery, dorsal region of body and head darker with black chromatophores. Body areas closer to anal-fin base, caudal and dorsal fin with scattered red chromatophores. Small dark chromatophores on premaxilla and lower jaw regions. Gray chromatophores aligned on dorsal margin of lower jaw region. Dark humeral spot on flank. Dorsal, anal and caudal fins vermilion red, with distal third hyaline and bearing scattered dark cromathophores. Adipose, pectoral and pelvic fins hyaline with scattered dark chromatophores.
